verbose_text: Type 2 diabetes was related to a significant increase in the levels of proinflammatory cytokines interleukin-6 (IL-6; P < 0.05 in both groups) and TNF-alpha (P < 0.05 without SMI and P < 0.01 with SMI) (XREF_TABLE) and higher levels of the adhesion molecules VCAM-1 and E-selectin (P < 0.05 without SMI and P < 0.01 with SMI).
evidence: levels of the adhesion molecules VCAM-1
